+{"id":"bd-1vr1.7","title":"Gateway unit tests: service layer real DB/WS (no mocks)","description":"Expand/convert service-layer tests (agent, reservation, dcg, safety, handoff, history, metrics, notifications) to run against the real sqlite DB + in-process hub rather than mocked modules. Use the shared harness for setup/teardown and deterministic runtime controls. Success: core services are exercised end-to-end in unit scope with zero mock.module usage.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:32.865277725Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T04:56:35.124378341Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T04:56:35.124309493Z","close_reason":"17 passing integration tests for history + DCG services against real SQLite DB with zero mock.module. Sets DB_FILE_NAME env before imports so services use temp DB. Tests cover createHistoryEntry, completeHistoryEntry, getHistoryEntry, queryHistory, getHistoryStats, exportHistory, extractFromOutput, getDcgConfig, updateDcgConfig, listPacks, ingestBlockEvent, getBlockEvents, markFalsePositive, getDcgStats.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.7","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.7","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.7","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.7","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.8","title":"Web unit tests: disable mock mode + use real API fixtures","description":"Ensure web unit tests run with mockMode=false and rely on real API fixtures from a test gateway instance (or deterministic seeded data). Replace any test assumptions that depend on mock data with real responses. Validate hooks (useSnapshot/useSafetyPosture/useVelocity) against live endpoints. Success: component/hook tests exercise real data flow rather than mock data branches.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:42.610726175Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:33:15.919220326Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.9","title":"Packages unit tests: agent-drivers + flywheel-clients without mocks","description":"Increase coverage in packages/agent-drivers and packages/flywheel-clients by exercising real command runners, file IO, and protocol parsing. Avoid mock.module and prefer temporary directories + real subprocess execution where feasible. Add integration tests for driver selection, capability detection, and client error handling. Success: package-level coverage is materially improved without fake drivers or mocked modules.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:53.224936354Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:33:23.183421887Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.9","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.9","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.9","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.9","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1w8f","title":"Ingest NTM robot alerts + mail into gateway snapshot","description":"Goal:\n- Integrate NTM robot alerts/mail into gateway alerting + snapshot.\n\nScope:\n- `ntm --robot-alerts` → gateway alerts.\n- `ntm --robot-mail` → snapshot mail section (read-only).\n\nDefinition of Done:\n- Snapshot includes NTM alerts/mail summaries.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-21T04:48:36.183109390Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-21T21:02:16.994072140Z","closed_at":"2026-01-21T21:02:16.993971731Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ntm","snapshot"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1w8f","depends_on_id":"bd-284u","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1w8f","depends_on_id":"bd-29in","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1w8f","depends_on_id":"bd-2h6i","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
